cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 45 mi NNW of Key West, Florida and 65 mi S of Naples, Florida
cyclone.trajectory: moving west-northwest into the southeastern Gulf of Mexico, then expected to slow, drift northward, and turn toward the northeast late week toward the Florida Big Bend/SE Georgia coast
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Big Bend coast (near Cedar Key–Steinhatchee area)

weather_observation.watch_coast: Tropical Storm Watch in effect for portions of western Cuba only
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical Storm Warning in effect for Florida Keys, much of the Florida peninsula coast, and the northwestern Bahamas
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Florida Keys, southern & central Florida peninsula, Gulf side of Florida, and eventually portions of the northern Florida and southeast Georgia coast
weather_observation.wind: Increasing northeast to east winds late Thursday into Friday with occasional tropical-storm-force gusts (30–40 mph) possible
weather_observation.storm_surge: No significant storm-surge inundation expected along the southeast Georgia coast based on current track and intensity forecast
weather_observation.rainfall: Periods of heavy showers possible Fri–Sat but current guidance suggests totals generally 1–3 inches
weather_observation.other_hazards: Elevated seas and rip-current risk for coastal and harbor approaches; isolated tornado risk cannot be ruled out if outer rain-bands reach Georgia coast
